w the policy on cuss words, but there's just one in this... I didn't think it'd matter too much if I left it there. ^^<br>
<br>
I stood frozen in the hallway<br>
As my parents screamed again.<br>
I should have moved, I knew that,<br>
But he found me there again.<br>
He dragged me to my bedroom,<br>
Told me not to leave again<br>
And smacked me on the head,<br>
To make sure I understood.<br>
Daddy screamed at Mommy,<br>
I thought every Daddy should.<br>
Their shadows played on the wall<br>
I thought the dancing dark was good.<br>
Mommy yelled at Daddy,<br>
She was really really brave,<br>
She yelled &quot;Don't you dare hit them,<br>
Damn it, I mean it this time, Dave.&quot;<br>
Then she came in to see me<br>
Asked me how well did I behave?<br>
I told her I was really good,<br>
Cause Santa told me too.<br>
She smiled at me and kissed me,<br>
We said our &quot;I love you&quot;s.<br>
Daddy didn't hit me for a while;<br>
Maybe a day, maybe one or two.<br>
Daddy took me to the park,<br>
He swung me on the tire swing,<br>
I loved the sound of creaking chains<br>
Cause they didn't make me sting.<br>
I hated when Daddy hit me<br>
But I thought it was a passing thing.<br>
I grew old when I was nine,<br>
The day my Daddy went to jail,<br>
I blamed myself for all that happened,<br>
When our family began to fail.<br>
But Daddy spent one night there,<br>
And I thought that family would prevail,<br>
But Daddy just left us again,<br>
I think I was the only one who cried.<br>
I asked Daddy to come home again,<br>
But the plea was simply denied,<br>
I was fragile then and shattered,<br>
Did Daddy just push me aside?<br>
But Daddy went to school,<br>
They told him why he hit,<br>
Then Daddy came home again,<br>
But it was only for a visit.<br>
He talked to me and cried with me<br>
In the park where we used to sit.<br>
I've never seen my dad cry,<br>
He was so vunerable then.<br>
He wasn't the Daddy who hit me,<br>
He was just like other men.<br>
Bewilderment came upon me,<br>
I was just a girl of ten.<br>
Daddy moved away <br>
To a little farming town,<br>
I didn't get to see him much,<br>
Only when Mom let me go down.<br>
Still even then I held my finest dream,<br>
That my family would always be around.<br>
But we never got the chance,<br>
I was thirteen when it happened.<br>
I felt the cold of divorce,<br>
How it started to impend.<br>
My finest dream was broken<br>
When our family came to an end.<br>
